# 🧮 13. Roman to Integer

🔗 [LeetCode Link]https://leetcode.com/problems/roman-to-integer/description/?envType=problem-list-v2&envId=eeudwo2i)

## ✅ Approach:
- Use a HashMap to give respective values
- check whether a small roman appeared before a large one and subtract and add it accordingly.

## ⏱️ Time Complexity:
- unknown

## 🔤 Code (Java):
```java
lass Solution {
    public int romanToInt(String s) {
        int roman_value=0;
        int i=0;
        int length=s.length();
        Map<Character,Integer> roman_numerals=new HashMap<>(){{
            put('I',1);
            put('V',5);
            put('X',10);
            put('L',50);
            put('C',100);
            put('D',500);
            put('M',1000);
        }};
        while(i<length){
            int temp=roman_numerals.get(s.charAt(i));
            if(i!=length-1 && temp<roman_numerals.get(s.charAt(i+1))){
                roman_value+=roman_numerals.get(s.charAt(i+1))-temp;
                i+=2;
            }
            else{
                roman_value+=temp;
                i++;
            }
        }
        return roman_value;
    }
}
